description: Vice President Harris took questions on inflation, immigration and the way she became the Democratic nominee from undecided voters in her first town hall.
title: Harris uses town hall to show empathy with Latino voters

description: Lack of enthusiasm for Harris “seems to be more pronounced with the brothers," Obama said while campaigning for her in Pittsburgh. He said Black men need to get behind Harris and get out to vote.
title: Obama, in blunt terms, tells Black men to get over their reluctance to support Harris

description: The deaths of five infants ages 1-3 months old occurred from 2012 to 2022. It's not the first time the New York-based company has had to remove products from the market following infant fatalities.
title: Fisher-Price recalls 2 million Snuga Swings after infant deaths

description: “We ended up with 126 tornado warnings” in Florida, Matthew Elliott, the warning coordination meteorologist at the National Weather Service’s Storm Prediction Center, told NPR.
title: There’s been 38 eyewitness-reported tornadoes in Florida: Why did Milton cause so many?

description: More than 3 million Floridians were without power after Milton. In some areas like Siesta Key, damage was severe. In Sarasota, many residents were thankful things were not worse.
title: Floridians survey Milton's damage and get ready for a lengthy recovery

description: The mogul, who was indicted and arrested on federal charges in September, will be tried in a Manhattan court next summer.
title: Sean ‘Diddy’ Combs trial date set

description: The housing market these days isn't easy. We want to hear from you about what it's like to buy or sell a home right now.
title: Are you in the process of buying or selling a home? We want to hear from you.

description: Han Kang is first Korean writer to win the award. The citation commended "her intense poetic prose that confronts historical traumas and exposes the fragility of human life."
title: South Korean author Han Kang wins 2024 Nobel Prize in literature

description: A severe solar storm is headed to Earth that could stress power grids even more as the U.S. deals with major back-to-back hurricanes, space weather forecasters said Wednesday.
title: Severe solar storm may stress power grids as U.S. deals with major hurricanes
